HEADWORD: Skee
<hw>Skee</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dan. <ets>ski</ets>;
Icel. <ets>sk⟦imac⟧<?/</ets> a billet of wood. See <er>Skid</er>.]</ety>
<def>A long strip of wood, curved upwards in front, used on the foot for
sliding; now usually spelled <asp>ski</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

